Description.LocalizedString: Nobody knows for sure what it looks like, but there are many theories.
Its otherworldly form would be the last thing its victims ever saw.
Even its victims’ belongings would disappear, with no sign of where they could have gone.
Nobody knows for sure what it looks like, and those that find out are never seen again.
Its unnatural form would be the last thing its victims ever saw.
Even its victims’ belongings would disappear, to be used for more ominous purposes.
An outcast, a free-spirit, a lover of all things dark and twisted.
Even when she was alone broadcasting her radio show, Sable liked to dress with flair.
Flecks of color danced with the darkness around her.
A misfit, a troublemaker, a daughter of absolute darkness.
Even in her deepest despair, Sable liked to dress with flair.
Flecks of blood danced with the carnage around her.
